results.name: adidas GSG Mule 032c Savannah
results.story: The 032C x adidas GSG Mule ‘Savanna’ delivers a minimalist slip-on that blends inspiration from contemporary fashion and outdoor gear. The latter is embodied through utilitarian tooling borrowed from the adidas GSG-9 boot, which the Berlin-based creative group propped up as a foundational influence. Up top, beige neoprene is reinforced with a suede forefoot overly and lined in soft textile. Dual adidas and 032c branding lands on the crimson-hued sockliner.

Parley x UltraBoost 21 'Non Dyed'
results.story: The Parley x adidas UltraBoost 21 ‘Non Dyed’ carries a breathable Primeknit upper made in part with recycled Parley Ocean Plastic and zero virgin polyester. The lightweight build is mounted on a full-length Boost midsole for responsive cushioning. Underfoot, adidas’ LEP Torsion system offers improved energy return by increasing forefoot stiffness, while a Stretchweb Continental rubber outsole delivers optimal grip. Parley branding lands on each sockliner and the tongue tag on the left shoe.

adidas GSG Mule 032c Black
results.story: The 032C x adidas GSG Mule ‘Core Black’ applies a stealthy one-note finish to a slip-on silhouette that draws twin inspirations from technical sportswear and 2000s fashion design. Stretchy neoprene is utilized on the upper, accented with tonal three-stripe branding and fortified with synthetic leather overlays. The smooth surfaces up top are contrasted by a sculpted rubber tooling, enhanced with Adiprene cushioning and modeled after the adidas GSG-9 boot.

Nike Cosmic Unity Apricot Agate
results.story: Inspired by the natural world, the Nike Cosmic Unity ‘Pomegranate’ highlights pastel hues on a performance basketball shoe built with 25% recycled materials by weight. Peach-colored textile is utilized throughout the upper, equipped with a plush tongue decorated with a pomegranate graphic. A scientific infographic on the sockliner reveals that the fruit’s rind was used to create some of the shoe’s coloring. The sneaker is mounted on a podular foam midsole that’s supplemented by a full-length Air Zoom Strobel.

results.name: UltraBoost 'Made To Be Remade'
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost ‘Made To Be Remade’ continues the German sportswear brand’s sustainability efforts with an eco-friendly build devoid of harmful dyes or glue. The uncaged Primeknit upper is formed with seamless construction for a comfortable, sock-like fit. A QR code atop the tongue is made to be scanned at the end of the sneaker’s life cycle, at which time adidas reclaims the materials to create a new pair of shoes. The lightweight build is mounted on a Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a translucent TPU outsole.

adidas GSG TR 032c Hi-Res Yellow
results.story: Designed in partnership with the Berlin-based creative collective, the 032C x adidas GSG TR ‘Pulse Lime’ applies a monochromatic lime green finish to a lifestyle silhouette crafted from neoprene and secured with drawcord lacing. Tonal leather overlays feature a reflective finish for added visibility in low-light conditions. Mismatched tongue tags display adidas and 032c branding, with the latter logo making a repeat appearance on the lateral heel. The lightweight build is supported by rugged trail-inspired tooling borrowed from the adidas GSG-9 boot.

New Balance Vision Racer Jaden Smith Natural
results.story: Continuing the Boston-based sportswear brand’s partnership with the actor and musician, the Jaden Smith x New Balance Vision Racer ‘Natural’ showcases neutral tones on a chunky and sustainable build. A heathered grey finish is applied to the fleece-like textile upper, constructed from 74% SPINNEX fiber, 16% recycled polyester and 10% Spandex. Speckled detailing covers the sneaker’s synthetic overlays and segmented midsole, reinforced with an icy translucent outsole inscribed with pink lettering that reads, ‘Do You See It Yet?’

results.name: adidas ZX 8000 1. FC Union Berlin
results.story: Limited to just 1,966 pairs worldwide, the FC Union Berlin x adidas ZX 8000 ‘Stadion An der Alten Försterei’ features a distinctive palette inspired by the professional German football club. The retro runner carries a white mesh upper with tan leather overlays and contrasting three-stripes in red and yellow. ‘Union’ is inscribed in block letters across the heel, while the green-hued interior lining gives the nod to the club’s home stadium. Iron lace jewels forged in southeast Berlin represent the final touch.

adidas Campus 80s South Park Towelie
results.story: The South Park x adidas Campus 80 ‘Towelie’ showcases a unique build inspired by the animated series’ talking towel character. The low-top makes use of a lavender terry-cloth upper with contrasting white leather on the Trefoil-branded heel tab and signature three-stripes. Each tongue is decorated with Towelie’s cartoon eyes, which become pink and bloodshot when exposed to UV light. The interior tongue is equipped with a stash pocket and inscribed with a pair of mismatched quotes: ‘Don’t Forget to Bring a Towel’ on the left shoe and ‘I Have No Idea What’s Going On’ on the right.

results.story: Made for big kids, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star Low GS Tie Dye ‘Spring Pink’ showcases a psychedelic print throughout the upper, constructed from 12oz canvas and lined in breathable mesh. Traditional Converse All Star branding lands on the woven tongue tag and the license plate that decorates the white rubber midsole. A matching white finish is applied to the outsole, featuring a customary diamond traction pattern for optimal grip.

results.story: The Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High Summer Wave ‘Washed Amber Ochre’ updates the foundational sneaker with a tie-dye print on the canvas upper. The diffuse pink and orange hues are offset by a solid white rubber midsole, accented with contrasting black pinstripes and a Converse All Star license plate. Wmns Gel Cumulus 23 'Aqua Angel'
results.story: The ASICS women’s Gel Cumulus 23 ‘Aqua Angel’ applies a monochromatic pastel finish to the engineered mesh upper, made with at least 20% recycled content and featuring targeted zones of support and breathability. The lightweight build is mounted on two layers of FlyteFoam cushioning. 3D Space Construction is built into the top layer for enhanced compression with each stride, while ASICS’ Gel technology in the heel delivers superior shock absorption.

results.name: Skycourt 'Earth Day'
results.story: The ASICS Skycourt 'Earth Day' showcases a neutral palette on a retro-inspired sneaker built with eco-friendly materials. 50% recycled materials make up the composition of the upper, which mimics the look of the Gel-Altitude volleyball shoe from 1990. Inside the shoe, the sockliner is manufactured via a solution dyeing process that uses less water while reducing carbon emissions. The low-top sits on a durable rubber cupsole modeled after the ASICS Japan S.

Wmns Gel Resolution 8 LE 'Earth Day'
results.story: The ASICS women’s Gel Resolution 8 LE ‘Earth Day’ updates the performance tennis shoe with a sustainable build. 40% of the cream-hued mesh upper is made with recycled materials, including pre-owned garments and leftover fabric scraps, while the sockliner is produced with a solution dyeing process that reduces water usage and carbon emissions. The sneaker rides on a springy FlyteFoam midsole with Gel cushioning in the forefoot and heel.
